			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nThis pull request addresses a null password handling issue in the encryption configuration screen and improves the visual styling of the Smalltalk UI elements. A guard clause prevents null password processing when users cancel the password prompt, whilst theme-based styles are applied to input fields, buttons, and page elements.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Encryption Configuration Guard** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/EncryptionConfigScreen/EncryptionConfigScreen.tsx`|Added early return check when newPassword is null to prevent proceeding with validation or toggle operations after user cancels the password prompt.|\n|**Smalltalk UI Theming** <br> `packages/app-desktop/main.scss`|Applied theme-based styling to Smalltalk UI elements including input fields, buttons, and page containers with support for hover, active, and focus states using CSS theme variables.|\n\n## Possibly related issues\n\n- **laurent22/joplin#14428**: The null password guard directly resolves the \"Cancel shows 'Encryption key is required'\" behaviour by preventing downstream operations when the password prompt is cancelled.\n\n## Suggested labels\n\n`desktop`, `bug`, `enhancement`\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 3</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (3 passed)</summary>\n\n|     Check name     | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                   |\n| :----------------: | :------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|     Title check 